  <section class="paragraph paragraph--type--embed-code paragraph--view-mode--default wwf-page-section">
          <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="wwf-full-width">
            
            <div class="field field-embed-code"><section class="mpx-newcopy paragraph paragraph--type--title-and-text paragraph--view-mode--default wwf-page-section">

  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-md-8">
        <div class="field-title">
          <h2 class="mpxH2">Tigers Come Roaring Back</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="mpx-paragraph field field-copy">
          <p>
            Global wild tiger numbers hit an all-time low in 2010, with an estimated 121 in Nepal.
            The tigers’ habitat faces pressure, for example from development such as road expansion
            and habitat use such as livestock grazing, while tiger poaching for the illegal wildlife
            trade also threatens their survival. With pressure on habitat, tigers are pushed into
            closer contact with people, which can result in tiger-human conflict. Tiger habitat is
            also affected by climate change with extreme weather events resulting in forest fires or
            flooding.
            <br><br>
            WWF has been working with local communities, other organisations and the government of
            Nepal to strengthen community-based tiger protection and monitoring efforts, and the
            management and restoration of vital tiger habitat. A shared vision was developed to
            double the number of wild tigers by 2022, the Lunar Year of the Tiger.
            <br><br>
            In July 2022, Nepal announced it has more than doubled the number of wild tigers to an
            estimate of 355 individuals. The success was only possible through a combination of
            efforts, for example from local communities to government.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<head>
<style>
  .mpx.paragraph.paragraph--type--title-and-text.paragraph--view-mode--default.wwf-page-section{
    background-color: #f89834;
  }

